    content: "The road from Montreal to Mont-Tremblant is one of the best drives in Quebec. The A-15 opens up north of Sainte-Agathe, the Laurentian hills close in, and if you have 500+ horsepower under your right foot, the whole experience becomes something else entirely. This is the drive you rent an exotic car for.\n\n**The Route**\n\nMontreal → Autoroute 15 North → Saint-Sauveur → Sainte-Agathe → Route 117 → Mont-Tremblant. Roughly 150km each way. In an RS7 or BMW M5, it takes about 90 minutes — and you'll want to take longer. The road between Sainte-Adèle and Mont-Tremblant has elevation changes, sweeping curves, and the kind of scenery that makes you forget you're in Canada.\n\n**Best Cars for This Drive**\n\nThe **Audi RS7** ($499/day) is the perfect grand tourer for this route — comfortable at speed, precise in corners, and it fits skis or luggage if you're staying the weekend. The **McLaren 600LT** ($1,199/day) is for those who want to feel every curve. The **Lamborghini Urus** ($849/day) handles the mountain roads beautifully while keeping everyone comfortable.\n\n**Mont-Tremblant Arrival**\n\nParking your McLaren or G63 in front of the Fairmont Tremblant or at the pedestrian village is an experience in itself. The mountain crowd appreciates good cars.\n\n**Book It**\n\nWhatsApp (514) 773-8079. Tell us your travel dates and preferred car. We deliver in Montreal before your departure or anywhere in the Laurentians with advance notice.",
